Punjab & Maharashtra Co-Op. Bank Embraces International Business Machines Corp Smarter Computing To Support Its Branch Expansion And Online Presence

Tuesday, 14 Aug 2012 08:01am EDT

Punjab & Maharashtra Co-op. Bank Ltd announced that it has selected International Business Machines Corp approach to IT to accelerate its growth and reach in the fast developing financial services landscape in India. PMC Bank chose to migrate its applications including core banking to an IBM infrastructure with Power Systems to support the growing needs of its more than 66 branches, two extension counters and ATM network, while strengthening its online presence through remote banking.Â 

